Encounter underway in J-K’s Pulwama, militants believed to be trapped inside a house 
9-3-2017 
An encounter is underway between security forces and militants in Jammu and Kashmir’s Padgampora in Pulwama district.

A group of militants is believed to be trapped inside a house.

Troops from 55 Rashtriya Rifles and Special Operation Group (SOG) of Awantipora police are involved in the operation.

This is the second major encounter in Kashmir in the last four days. On Sunday, two militants and a policeman were killed in south Kashmir’s Tral in a gunfight that began Saturday evening and continued over night.

The slain cop was identified as Manzoor Ahmed Naik. He was a native of Salamabad area of Uri. 
